# TODO [CRITICAL][DevOps]:
# NEXTAUTH_SECRET uses a placeholder value "your-super-secret-key-change-this-in-production"
# This placeholder might accidentally be used in production if the env var is not set.
# Fix: Add startup validation that rejects this specific placeholder value.
# Generate a strong secret: openssl rand -base64 32
# Risk: Weak/predictable NEXTAUTH_SECRET allows JWT forgery.

# TODO [CRITICAL][DevOps]:
# DATABASE_URL uses SQLite for dev. Production MUST use PostgreSQL.
# This file should document both configurations clearly.
# Risk: Deploying with SQLite DATABASE_URL in production causes data loss under load.

# TODO [HIGH][DevOps]:
# PayPlus credentials are not documented here (PAYPLUS_API_KEY, PAYPLUS_SECRET_KEY,
# PAYPLUS_PAYMENT_PAGE_UID). If a developer sets up a new environment, they won't
# know these variables are required and payments will silently fail.
# Fix: Add ALL required environment variables to this file with clear descriptions.
# Risk: Incomplete env configuration causes cryptic runtime errors.

# TODO [HIGH][DevOps]:
# No environment variable validation on application startup.
# Fix: Add src/env.ts using @t3-oss/env-nextjs or zod schema validation.
# This file should be imported in next.config.js to fail fast on startup.
# Risk: Missing env vars cause runtime crashes instead of startup failures.

# TODO [MEDIUM][DevOps]:
# No distinction between required and optional environment variables.
# Fix: Annotate each variable as REQUIRED or OPTIONAL with a default value.
# Risk: Developers don't know which variables must be set for minimum viable deployment.

# Database - SQLite for local dev, PostgreSQL for PRODUCTION
# TODO [CRITICAL][DevOps]: Change to PostgreSQL for production:
# DATABASE_URL="postgresql://user:password@localhost:5432/poker_israel"
DATABASE_URL="file:./dev.db"

# NextAuth - REQUIRED - Generate: openssl rand -base64 32
# TODO [CRITICAL][Security]: Never use this placeholder in production!
NEXTAUTH_URL="http://localhost:3000"
NEXTAUTH_SECRET="your-super-secret-key-change-this-in-production"

# TODO [HIGH][DevOps]: Add all missing required environment variables:

# PayPlus Payment Integration - REQUIRED for payments
# PAYPLUS_API_KEY="your-payplus-api-key"
# PAYPLUS_SECRET_KEY="your-payplus-secret-key"
# PAYPLUS_PAYMENT_PAGE_UID="your-payment-page-uid"

# Application URL - REQUIRED
# NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL="https://yourdomain.com"

# TODO [MEDIUM][DevOps]: Add these for production infrastructure:

# Error Tracking - RECOMMENDED
# SENTRY_DSN="https://your-sentry-dsn"

# Rate Limiting (Upstash Redis) - REQUIRED for security
# UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL="https://..."
# UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_TOKEN="..."

# Email Service (Resend) - REQUIRED for email verification & notifications
# RESEND_API_KEY="re_..."
# EMAIL_FROM="noreply@yourdomain.com"

# Image Storage (Cloudinary) - REQUIRED after image migration
# CLOUDINARY_CLOUD_NAME="..."
# CLOUDINARY_API_KEY="..."
# CLOUDINARY_API_SECRET="..."

# Analytics - OPTIONAL
# NEXT_PUBLIC_POSTHOG_KEY="phc_..."
# NEXT_PUBLIC_POSTHOG_HOST="https://app.posthog.com"
